[6] Pakistan (Lahore)
Date: Sat 13 Apr 2013
Source: The News Tribe [edited]
http://www.thenewstribe.com/2013/04/13/2-more-die-as-measles-death-toll-in-punjab-touches-40-mark/


Another fatal outbreak of measles has claimed 4 lives in the province of Punjab. The children died in the Meo hospital of the provincial capital Lahore on Saturday [13 Apr 2013]. According to hospital sources, the ages of the infants ranged from 2 to 4 years, and they belonged to the Rawi road and Mari Pora areas.

The total number of lives lost to measles in Lahore has increased to 40, while the number of those affected in the province has risen to 8350.

In a deadly outbreak last year [2012], a large number of lives were lost due primarily to a lack of appropriate vaccination in the country.

[Byline: Hassa Siddiqui]

